## 🛠️ 6. Essential Linux Commands Reference

| Category | Command | Description | Example Usage |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Directory Navigation** | `cd` | Change the current directory | `cd /var/log` |
| | `cd ..` | Move up one directory level | `cd ..` |
| **Print Working Directory**| `pwd` | Displays the absolute path of current folder | `pwd` |
| **File & Folder Management**| `ls` | List directory contents | `ls -la` |
| | `mkdir` | Create a new folder | `mkdir thm-labs` |
| | `touch` | Create a new empty file | `touch notes.txt` |
| | `cp` | Copy files or directories | `cp notes.txt backup/` |
| | `mv` | Move or rename files/folders | `mv notes.txt final.txt` |
| | `rm` | Delete a file (`-r` for folders) | `rm -rf old-folder` |
| **Viewing & Editing Files**| `cat` | View entire file contents in terminal | `cat final.txt` |
| | `less` | View file content with page scrolling | `less syslog` |
| | `head` / `tail` | View the top or bottom lines of a file | `tail -n 20 auth.log` |
| | `nano` / `vim` | Terminal-based text editors | `nano configuration.conf` |
| **System & Admin Priv.** | `sudo` | Execute a command with root privileges | `sudo apt update` |
| | `chmod` | Modify file/directory permissions | `chmod +x script.sh` |
| | `chown` | Change file/directory ownership | `sudo chown root system.log` |
| **Networking Commands** | `ifconfig` / `ip a` | View network interface configurations | `ip a` |
| | `ping` | Test connectivity to a host | `ping -c 4 8.8.8.8` |
| | `netstat` / `ss` | Display active network connections & ports | `ss -tulpn` |

